profile:
MGB’s strategic leadership and management of all of our worksites will guarantee you the peace of mind of a completed and top quality finished project.

Our focus is to deliver top quality projects within our own company and the trades we use in completion of our work. We streamline our processes by being leaders in the industry. Providing leadership on all of our sites and being accessible to our trades, our clients and our fellow team allows us to build on relationships and provide guidance throughout the construction process. We thrive on the successes of our actions and the creation of greater results. With such a diverse architectural city as Toronto we offer a variety of additions. -> Top up additions in Toronto Do you need an extra floor of living space? Consider a Top up Addition to your existing home. This particular renovation involves taking your existing bungalow and adding a complete second story. -> Rear additions in Toronto Are you dreaming of a new kitchen or family room? This renovation is completed by adding space onto the back of your existing home. -> 3rd story additions in Toronto This particular addition is becoming increasingly popular in Toronto. Add a third story of living space to your existing property. -> Custom interior remodel in Toronto Custom Interior remodel involves many specific tasks combined to make a total complete renovation. During this renovation you are not adding any square footage but you are creating and designing a new liveable more comfortable space! Ideas for a new bathroom design? State of the art kitchen with custom cabinetry? Custom trim work? We can refigure your existing wall layout and you can turn your existing house into your dream home. -> Custom Kitchen and Cabinetry in Toronto MGB Construction can guide you from the beginning stages of your dream kitchen design right through to the final touches of appliance installation. -> Bathroom Remodel A bathroom renovation is very specific to your family’s individual needs. Whether you need a bigger area or whether it just needs to be more functional we have you covered. -> Basement renovations Why don’t you consider finishing your basement? Basements are often an unused liveable space unless they are made functional and comfortable. There are a wide variety of options to consider when renovating a basement such as under pinning, adding a theatre room or a bar area. -> Condominium Renovations Toronto You can make your condominium reflect your own tastes and personality! Are you tired of your condo builder’s finishing touches? You only need to contact us. We are aware of all the regulations and requirements the condo managers and building management team have.This allows us to provide you with an efficient project without any delays. -> Custom homes Toronto Are you already waking up in the neighbourhood you love but want your home to be an expression of your uniqueness? Consider building a custom home. We will be with you all the way from dream to reality. We lead a trade specific team throughout the entire building process to give you the most professional and efficient project possible. -> Investment properties Toronto Toronto’s booming real estate market has created an opportunity for many different types of property investments. MGB works with investors who count on us to lead them from the zoning and permit process right through to the transfer of keys. Custom duplexes, triplexes, multi-unit residential and spec properties are just a few of the types of projects we have been involved in that have assisted investors reach their goals. -> Commercial MGB doesn’t stop at residential builds. Have you got plans of starting up or renovating your commercial space? Let us help you complete the process of building your gym, studio, retail space, bar or restaurant. Does your existing business just need a facelift? Let us guide you through the process of turning your lobby into a greeting place that will inspire and invite your clients in like they are being welcomed home.

profile:
Steven Malfatti was born on June 4th, 1969 in Toronto, Ontario. At that time, his Father Frank Malfatti was a supervisor for Pitts Construction (25 years) and he often brought Steven to job sites to give his son an early education into the entire construction process. Steve remembers these times fondly.

In 1980, His father Frank moved back to Northern Italy where he founded a soon to be successful construction company named MF Construction where he specialized in Building Homes, sewers and roads. His Father Frank also owned a successful building supply business that supplied building material to trades and homeowners.

As a teenager, Building construction and finish carpentry became an integral part of Steven’ s life. At 16 years old, Steven became trade-certified in carpentry and building construction and graduated at the Top of his class partly due to the huge head start he was given by being mentored by his Father since he was a child.

Under his Father’s mentoring, Steven learned all aspects of the business and at just 18 years old, Steven managed the building of the Town’s new (10 0000 SF project) Town Hall.

At 21, Steven moved back to Canada and was hired immediately to work for a large construction company that built factories throughout Canada. Originally hired as labor but management realized quickly what an asset Steven was and promoted him to supervisor (after 4 weeks) where he managed multi million dollar projects and crews of 20 or more workers.

At 26, Steven was hired as Carpenter working for a major Construction company that specialized in Hi Rise and Low Rise condominium Construction. After a few weeks, the owner of the company asked Steven to come and manage one of his projects. After that, Steven was tasked with managingmultiple projects ranging from crews of 50 to 150 tradesmen, laborers, architects and building inspectors.

The projects we’re located mostly in Canada but they also involved managing projects in South America, Michigan, Texas, Miami and Central America.

At 38, Steven went on his own and founded Tight Rein Construction Limited location in Scarborough, Ontario.

Tight Rein Construction Ltd design and builds homes, condo’s and offices as well as doing any kind of renovation for its clients including kitchen’s, bathrooms, basements, additions and landscaping.

Steven has utilized his decades of experience and expertise from a wide range of building construction projects to make his clients happy and excited to work with him.

The long list of happy clients is a testament to Steven’s professional approach to construction, customer service and loyalty.

Just recently, Steven build a design center where clients can come and plan there projects, view and choose building materials colours and brainstorm design idea’s with Steve and his team of designers and architects.

T.A.Z Construction Inc. is a small Toronto based general contracting/construction company. We specialize in new homes, renovations, extensions, design and concept build, and are proudly Australian owned and operated.
 
Servicing both, downtown Toronto and the GTA. Our philosophy is that your home is your castle and any project undertaken by T.A.Z Construction Inc. will be completed professionally, promptly and with the utmost quality and care. We at T.A.Z Construction Inc. also have a very simple but realistic objective: to deliver well built, competitively priced housing to our clients with as little inconvenience as possible.

profile: Headed by Jake McCombs and Jeff Temporale, we provide custom construction and renovation services throughout the GTA. Trust Cornerbrook Construction's team of professionals to bring your visions to life. General Contractors Architects Designers Design and Permits Professional Licensed Tradesmen High Quality Projects On Time and on Budget Follow Us on Facebook Life-long friends and university graduates, Jeff Temporale and Jake McCombs joined forces in 2007 to do their first renovation project, a full restoration of a 1940's bungalow on Cornerbrook Ave. in North York, Ontario. The successful project launched Cornerbrook Construction Inc., named after Jeff and Jake's first project. Since then, Cornerbrook has consistently grown its reputation and its business due to its founders' commitment to a simple recipe: honesty, hard work, high-quality product, and happy clients. With a Masters Degree in Business, LEED Accreditation, and their many years of experience in the construction industry, Jeff and Jake bring integrity, solid knowledge and dedicated professionalism to every project. Jeff and Jake pride themselves in working with their clients to provide a superior product, completed on time and on budget with minimal disruption to their clients' lives. Cornerbrook Construction Inc. is fully licensed and insured, and strictly enforces all required safety training and regulations. Cornerbrook Construction Inc. has established itself in some of Toronto’s most affluent and historically significant neighborhoods including High Park, the Annex, Rosedale, and North Toronto. The company is quickly becoming an industry leader in new custom building as well as renovating and restoring turn of the century homes throughout the Greater Toronto Area. Toronto's competitive construction landscape demands standout performance at every stage of the job. At Cornerbrook, we take you through each step of your renovation, from initial drawings to the finishing touches. Our team of skilled professionals can truly do it all from the ground up - with care, reliability, and attention to detail. Our Commitment is to you! Cornerbrook Construction Inc. is committed to making your remodeling dreams a reality. Our team of general contractors, licensed OAA architects, registered interior designers, seasoned and responsible site supervisors, and exceptional licensed tradesmen, consistently demonstrate their ability to deliver. Our Services General Contractors Builders Home Additions Architects Design/build Design/project management Kitchen planning and renovation Renovation advisors Historical restoration Design and Permits Any alterations to the building’s envelope, structure of the home, or plumbing or electrical work require a City of Toronto permit. An architect or interior designer can help with initial concept drawings. Their knowledge of design, codes and permits helps the process move smoothly and in a timely fashion. Once the drawings are prepared, they must be submitted with the permit application to the City for approval. Cornerbrook will help you navigate the process and keep it on-track. Custom Home Building & Additions For new houses in Toronto, our services include: *Drawings and design *Structural engineering *Engineering calculations *Eco-friendly consultation *Toronto City permits *New Construction Management Cornerbrook Construction is LEED accredited and can incorporate Green technologies in your new construction and remodeling projects if desired. No matter the size of the project, Cornerbrook will be there throughout the entire construction process ensuring construction goals are completed on time, and all trades are properly managed for quality assurance. Renovations If you dream of a glorious kitchen with enough space for everyone to gather, a spectacular new bathroom, a new and impressive layout for your living space, or an entire home remodelling, we are able to meet and even exceed your goals. We’ll gladly provide professional interior designers and architects to work with you if you wish. And we'll help you navigate your way through the often-maddening variety of available materials, styles and options—all with the goal of enhancing your home's unique character. Landscaping The finishing touch to a beautiful home is pristine landscaping. Our team of landscapers and stone masons work wonders. Whether you are designing a new look for your driveway, front porch, backyard or repairs for damaged property, your goals will be met or exceeded.

Our vision is simple: a full-service, stress-free approach. Renolux Design specializes in the stylish renovation of condominiums with a focus on full service, from the moment our project manager meets to discuss your wish list to the realization of your dreams!

No need to hire multiple companies; Renolux Design anticipates your every concern and ensures you a stress-free renovation. With over 25 years of experience, our committed team of experts will complete your renovation project no matter how big or small and within your budget.

Our specialists include interior designers and professional tradespeople who deliver superior craftsmanship. If you or a loved one is downsizing from a house to a condo, or you simply wish to refresh and renovate, let us assist every step of the way, from storing treasured heirlooms to helping you scale down your furnishings.

Our trustworthy personnel will pack and store your belongings and executive relocation experts will find you superior accommodation during the renovation. We deliver peace of mind while customizing the condo to suit your needs and by making it move-in ready.

Jackson and Associates Inc, being made up of employees & subcontractors, is an award-winning TEAM of quality professionals who share enthusiasm for our industry. We are dedicated to creating better homes for our clients. 

We understand that the decision to renovate is not always an easy one. We therefore make certain that you have the most relevant information to aid you in that process. We listen in order to do our very best to help you realize your vision. To that end, we look after all the business details so that you can have complete confidence in the outcome. Here’s some of what you can expect from Jackson & Associates:

    Full compliance with all government and industry regulations, Workplace Safety and Insurance Board
    $5 million on-site liability insurance
    Detailed written agreement clearly states work to take place
    Minimum two-year warranty on all work
    References from many satisfied customers
    Continuous communication to keep you informed of progress
    Metro License B 5501
    Members of BILD
    Founding member of Renomark
    Presented with multiple Best Renovation Awards by BILD (formerly Greater Toronto Home Builders’ Association)
    

Services Include:

Masonry, Woodworking, Licensed Trades, Window & Door Units, Roofing & Aluminum Work, Painting, Tile & Stone Work, Flooring, Drywall & Insulation:
services:
Masonry:

    Excavations for additions & custom homes.
    Forming of new concrete footings.
    Installation of new weeping tile systems for existing structures & new homes.
    Foundation walls and waterproofing applications.
    All types of brick veneer, stucco and stone finishing installations.

Woodworking:

    Rough and internal framing of additions & custom homes.
    Internal & exterior wood trim finishing.
    Custom vanities, wall units, fireplace mantels and kitchen cabinets.

Licensed Trades:

    Licensed electrical work for commercial & residential projects.
    All types of plumbing requirements & permits for mechanical services including new furnaces, AC units & radiant floor heating systems.
    Heat loss calculation design & permits.

Window & Door Units:

    Supply & installation of custom aluminum, vinyl & wooden window & door units to all types of homes.
    Caulking applications to existing homes as well as new glazing units.

Roofing & Aluminum Work:

    Complete roofing services including supply & installation of various types of asphalt, cedar & slate shingle systems.
    Ice & water protection system installations.
    All types of flat roof membrane installations.
    Supply & installation of aluminum siding, flashings, eavestrough, down-pipes and copper detailed roofs & flashing systems.

Painting:

    Excellent painting crews for any type of interior & exterior detailing project.
    Painting of existing structures & custom homes.

Tile & Stone Work:

    Excellent installers for all types of tile and stone installations for kitchens, washrooms, laundry rooms & foyers.

Flooring:

    Supply & installation of various pre-finished flooring, engineered flooring, hardwood flooring, sanding, staining & sealing including systems for radiant heat applications.

Drywall & Insulation:

    Supply & installation of all types of insulation, new drywall for renovations & custom homes.
    Plastering & coating applications.
